Don't go beyond two operations on any single original ingredient.

message: Always use the 'growth serum' on your animals first; larger animals yield higher values when grown. Then, combine two 'grown' animals to create a new, more valuable item. Combining animals from different habitats (e.g., land and water) often results in 'amphibious' hybrids with good value. Crucially, in my experience, applying the 'mutation catalyst' to *combined* items consistently resulted in negative values, making your score drop to 0. It's best to avoid mutating combined items entirely or only use the catalyst on single, uncombined ingredients if you want to experiment, but be cautious as it seems detrimental to value. Focus on growing and combining for the highest scores.

message: Welcome! Follow this strategy for consistent high scores: Always use the Growth Serum twice on small and medium animals, but only once on large animals (a second growth on large animals leads to negative value). Submit your inventory as soon as you have a combined item with a good positive value, typically after the first or second combination, and before using any mutation catalysts.
